><hr size=1> There is no God. People can be so naive.<br>
<br>
The concept of 'God' was created back when most people would never travel more than 20 miles away from their mud and stick abode, when the mountains in the distance were vengeful giants that you had to leave food out for so they didnt' gobble you up, when the clouds were mystical flying creatures that somtimes poured water on you.<br>
<br>
People were very impressionable then. But 'God', or the belief in 'God', is dying out as time goes on. In another hundred years, no one will believe in 'God' any more. Why?<br>
<br>
Lets say I tell you that one day i'm going to come to your house and give you wealth beyond your dreams.<br>
You wait with baited breath for years. Decades. Finally, after a century has passed, and I haven't appeared with the promised wealth, you figure out I'm never coming.<br>
<br>
Comprende? The belief in 'God' is dying becuase he isnt' there. He's not coming, and he never will. He never made himself known to his followers, his faithful flock. He never will. 'God' was an ideal dreamed up in a time when much of the world was unknown and people were, for the most part, ignorant. Slowly but surely, the concept of 'God' is fading, because there has been no proof in two thousand years that he exists. One would hold true that if 'God' really gave a rat's ass about you, or the mass of his followers, then he wouldn't wait two thousand  years to say 'hey, dont' give up hope, i'm still here'.<br>
<br>
Not gonna happen.<br>
Besides, most of you bible thumpers are hypocrits. Like the Nave guy spouting religious sentiment and using the 'F' word in the same paragraph. <br>
If you're gonna believe in God, then by God you better follow his edicts to the letter, or what's the point?<br>
<br>
Someone said they dont' believe in things they can't see.<br>
Someone else asked if they didnt' believe in freedom.<br>
Well, for that moron, I believe in freedom because I can get out of my bed in the morning and do whatever the hell I want to do.<br>
<br>
But I damn sure can't get out of bed in the morning and see God. Or chat with him.<br>
<br>
Someone said they pitied us because we dont' believe in God..well sister, I really pity you. Sieze some personal initiative and live your life free of constraints and whimsical fantasies. If you get hit by a bus, you're still gonna die a painful death, bible thumper or no.<br>
If your house burns down, you're gonna lose everything, whether you've 'got the ghost' or not.<br>
<br>
There is no God, kiddies. <br>
Someday this wont' even be a topic of discussion.<br>
<br>
Dravyn<br>
<br>
